    "narrative": "Today\u2019s rotation for LawDog is headlined by **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, who boasts an elite 84.25 score against the left-handed Perez. The combination of his massive base projection and a significant SP skill bonus (+19%) makes him the anchor of our lineup. Following him, **Lawrence Butler** (73.47) is a priority start. Despite a slight park penalty, his leadoff spot and a strong platoon edge (+13%) against Senga make him a high-upside play for stolen base production, a critical need given our current roster constraints. **Bryson Stott** (69.44) also gains substantial value today; he benefits from Pfaadt\u2019s slow delivery, which provides a tangible boost to his theft potential, aligning perfectly with our mandate to hunt scarcity.\n\nTactical park factors are driving the middle tier of our lineup. **Luis Arraez**, **Jung Hoo Lee**, and **Matt Chapman** all receive a massive 16% park-factor bump today against Bassitt, keeping their efficiency scores well within the \"Strong\" range despite facing a capable arm. The most difficult decision rested between the outfielders and our bench. **Taylor Ward** was the hardest player to cut (48.65); while he benefits from the same favorable park environment as **Arraez**, he was benched because his efficiency plummeted against Webb, whose elite skill neutralized the park advantage. We are keeping a close watch on **Cal Raleigh** and **Brendan Donovan**; both are currently \"Lineup Pending,\" and should they shift to the bottom of the order, their efficiency scores will drop, though they remain locked in barring an extreme change in team construction.",
